author: JOSHUA McKEEVER Special to the Daily News
title: Mohave keeps rolling
text:
Mohave keeps rolling By JOSHUA McKEEVER Special to the Daily News MohaveDailyNews.com | 0 comments 
BULLHEAD CITY — The Lady T-birds defeated the Yuma Catholic High School Lady Shamrocks 25-21, 21-25, 25-14, 25-17 at Mohave High School on Thursday night. 
“It was a truly exciting game,” T-birds head coach Zdenko Radic said. “I don’t know where to start actually. Kind of this was our second game this week, and we played two days ago, had a really good game, came from behind and Yuma Catholic is really good.” 
Radic said his T-birds played the Shamrocks in a tournament game at Lake Havasau High School earlier this season. 
“We knew if we didn’t step it up and play our best game, it would be really tough,” Radic said. “But, I’m really proud of the girls because they started to play smart from the first point to the end of the game, they never laid down, they played like they were the best team.” 
The 17-2 overall Arizona Interscholastic Association Division IV, Section III Lady T-birds remained undefeated in their section at 4-0. Yuma Catholic is now 7-7 overall, and 1-3 in Section III, according to aiaonline.org and maxpreps.com .
